ce:section.ce:para:
The reaction of 1-naphthol with 4-hydroxybenzaldehyde and malononitrile was chosen as model reaction for screening the catalytic ability of CQD-CRS (Scheme 2
                        ). CQD-CRS was prepared by adding an aqueous solution of IL-1 (195nM) or IL-2 (17nM) to an aqueous solution of CQDs, whereby the final concentration of IL-1 and IL-2 was maintained above the CMC. 1-Naphthol (1 equiv), 4-hydroxybenzaldehyde (1 equiv), and malononitrile (1 equiv) were then added to the aqueous solution of CQD-CRS. The reaction mixture was sonicated at room temperature. During the reaction, a small fraction of the solution was taken at intervals of 3min. Water was added to the fraction, which was filtered, dried, and analyzed by 1H NMR. The results are summarized in Table 1
                        . In the case of IL-1, the reaction was completed in 15min with a yield of 97%. IL-2 was found to be comparatively more efficient than IL-1 as the reaction reached completion in 12min. Since IL-2 possesses a longer chain hydrophobic group, it can form a larger hydrophobic cavity in the micelles than IL-1, providing more space to accommodate the reactants.
